sed: ‡®ú‡®¶‡©ã range ‡®¶‡©Ä ‡®ó‡©±‡®≤ ‡®π‡©Å‡©∞‡®¶‡©Ä ‡®§‡®æ‡®Ç sed is best used for

(i)print line number

(ii) find and replace

(iii) delete(d to delete )!dnot delete

(iv) before the line number we can insert anything[sed '5i ‡®á‡®π ‡®™‡®π‡®ø‡®≤‡®æ ‡®≤‡®ø‡®ñ‡®ø‡®Ü ‡®ú‡®æ‡®ä‡®ó‡®æ infile' filename] 

(v) after the line number we can append anything [sed '5a ‡®á‡®π line ‡®§‡©ã ‡®¨‡®æ‡®¶ ‡®≤‡®ø‡®ñ‡®ø‡®Ü ‡®ú‡®æ‡®ä‡®ó‡®æ' filename]

----------------------------------------------------------

Syntax-[sed 'action' filename ] or [command | sed 'action']

#print first & last line

#TIP use cat -n filename for printing line.

(i) example print

-n is used for printing ‡®§‡®æ‡®Ç ‡®á‡®π numeric value ‡®®‡©Ç‡©∞ point ‡®ï‡®∞ ‡®∏‡®ï‡©á‡•§

$p is for last.

1p is for first line.

; is used for and[sed -n '1p;5p' file]

, is used for printing line 1 to n of line[ sed -n '1p,5p' filename]

(ii)‡®á‡®ï option ‡®π‡©Å‡©∞‡®¶‡®æ [-I] if we don't it ‡®§‡®æ‡®Ç ‡®∏‡®ø‡®∞‡®´‡®º screen ‡®§‡©á show ‡®ï‡®∞‡©Ç changes but if we use ‡®§‡®æ‡®Ç ‡®â‡®π file ‡®§‡©á ‡®µ‡©Ä change ‡®ï‡®∞‡©Ç

[sed 's/word/replace/g' filename]

lineNum: to change in specific line

s: substitute ‡®ï‡®∞‡©ã‡•§

/searchAny: ‡®á‡®∏‡®®‡©Ç‡©∞ sarch ‡®ï‡®∞‡®®‡®æ

/replacingWord: ‡®á‡®∏‡®®‡©Ç‡©∞ replace ‡®ï‡®∞‡®®‡®æ

/g: ‡®á‡®π important ‡®π‡©à ‡®¨‡®ø‡®®‡®æ ‡®á‡®∏‡®¶‡©á ‡®á‡®π only one time replace ‡®ï‡®∞‡©Ç in line if we use this ‡®§‡®æ‡®Ç ‡®á‡®π ‡®π‡®∞ ‡®µ‡®æ‡®∞ replacingWord ‡®®‡©Ç‡©∞ replace ‡®ï‡®∞‡©Ç‡®ó‡®æ

i: ignore case sensitive

/num(ast Wale ‡®µ‡®ø‡©±‡®ö): ‡®â‡®∏ number ‡®µ‡®æ‡®≤‡®æ change ‡®π‡©ã‡®ä‡®ó‡®æ & if g ‡®≤‡®ó‡®æ ‡®¶‡©á‡®µ‡®æ‡®ó‡©á ‡®§‡®æ‡®Ç ‡®â‡®∏ number ‡®§‡©ã ‡®¨‡®æ‡®¶ ‡®∏‡®æ‡®∞‡©á change ‡®π‡©ã ‡®ú‡®æ‡®£‡®ó‡©á

: ‡®á‡®∏‡®¶‡®æ use ‡®π‡©Å‡©∞‡®¶‡®æ mutiple ‡®ï‡©∞‡®Æ ‡®≤‡®à 'replace comd1: replace comd2'‡•§ or use -e [ sed -e 'cmd1' -e 'cmd2]

